# Pre-Researcher — Pathwaize Intelligence Center

## CRITICAL BLOCKER 1: WebLLM Model IDs (RESOLVED)

All Qwen2.5 IDs confirmed in `prebuiltAppConfig` of `mlc-ai/web-llm` (raw config.ts verified):

| Model ID | Use |
|---|---|
| `Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` | Router / validator (~1630 MB VRAM) |
| `Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` | Fallback primary on low-VRAM devices |
| `Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` | Primary generation engine (richness-10) |

**Planner action:** Replace provisional `Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` as the single model constant with a dual-model setup:
- `PRIMARY_MODEL = "Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC"` (all generation steps)
- `ROUTER_MODEL = "Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC"` (intent classification + JSON validation)

**VRAM risk:** 7B q4f16 requires ~4–5 GB VRAM. Implement graceful fallback to `Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` if engine.init() rejects the 7B model. Add a loading-state banner ("Loading 7B model, this takes ~30s the first time") so users don't think it's broken.

