## HIGH: GHL Iframe Context (RESOLVED for proposal purposes)

- Custom pages render **full-width** in GHL's main content area (typically 1100–1400px available desktop width; sidebar is ~64px collapsed or ~220px expanded)
- Auth context passed via **URL query params**: `?locationId={{location.id}}&userId={{user.id}}` or signed context token
- Must NOT set `X-Frame-Options: DENY`; CSP must include `frame-ancestors: https://*.gohighlevel.com https://app.gohighlevel.com`
- GHL has both light and dark dashboard themes (agency-customizable); iframe content is fully isolated from GHL chrome — no shared CSS variables
- **Demo approach:** Render as standalone with a mock GHL chrome wrapper (thin dark top bar labelled "Pathwaize Intelligence Center | GoHighLevel") to simulate embedding context

**Proposal copy:** Describe iframe integration as: "Hosted on your domain, embedded as a Custom Menu Link or Marketplace App iframe inside GHL with zero-config OAuth context passing (locationId, userId). No GHL whitelabel restrictions — ships as a sub-account custom page."

---

## SHOULD: Competitor UI Differentiation

Jasper and Copy.ai both use light-mode, template-card-centric UIs. Differentiators for the Intelligence Center:

1. **Run console metaphor** (not a template gallery): Engines are launched, not browsed. Primary action is "Run Engine" button with real-time status streaming.
2. **Approval gates as first-class UI** (not an afterthought): Output cards have inline [Approve] / [Request Edits] / [Re-run] controls — the workflow IS the UI.
3. **Status chip pipeline** (6-state system already in plan): Idle → Running → Pending Review → Approved → Pushed → Error — visible at all times.
4. **Prompt chip bar** (persistent at bottom): Always-present context inputs (business name, niche, tone) that pre-fill all engine prompts — feels like a persistent "intelligence layer" not a chat box.

---

## SHOULD: Real Estate SaaS Visual Conventions

- Dark dashboards with high-contrast data tables are standard in proptech/investor tools (DealMachine, BatchLeads, PropStream all use dark accents)
- Status indicators: colored badges with terse labels (not long status text)
- Dense information layout — operators want data visible without scrolling
- Quick action buttons prominent above fold
- Mobile responsiveness less critical than desktop power-user experience for this use case

---

## Testing Approach

- **WebGPU availability gate:** On load, check `navigator.gpu` — if undefined, show a banner "WebGPU required. Use Chrome 113+ or Edge 113+" and disable run buttons
- **Model load progress:** Display download progress bar (WebLLM emits progress callbacks); cache to Origin Private File System (OPFS) via MLC's built-in caching — subsequent loads are instant
- **JSON schema enforcement:** Use `response_format: { type: "json_object" }` for all tool-call steps; validate in JS before proceeding; 1-retry reflection loop on failure
- **Structured output fallback:** If model returns invalid JSON after retry, surface a "Generation failed — try re-running" inline error card (not a page crash)
- **IndexedDB persistence:** Run history, output storage, approved items — all in IndexedDB; no network calls required for core workflow

---

## APIs / Integrations (V1 Scope)

Per brief, these should be **simulated with realistic mock responses** in the demo (not real integrations — no OAuth setup needed for proposal demo):
- Google Drive "push" → mock success toast + file card
- GitHub commit "push" → mock PR card with fake SHA
- Newsletter "send" → mock "Queued for review" state

Real integration stubs should be structured so a real OAuth token can be swapped in post-contract.

---

## Risks / Flags for Planner

1. **7B model on integrated GPU laptops:** 7B q4f16 may OOM on 4GB integrated GPUs (some MacBook Airs). Implement auto-detection: query WebGPU adapter info; if `adapterInfo.description` matches low-VRAM patterns, default to 3B. Display "Running compact model for your hardware" — not a failure state.
2. **First-load latency:** 7B model is ~4GB download. Must show prominent progress bar or users will close tab thinking it's broken. MLC caches to OPFS so second load is <5s.
3. **GHL postMessage API:** No formal spec for parent↔iframe communication in GHL marketplace apps. For the demo, simulate the context with URL params. In production, the developer would need GHL developer access to test signed context.
4. **Pathwaize has NO public design tokens** — the hex palette above is derived from industry conventions + the "execution console" brief language, not official brand guidelines. This is fine since the Intelligence Center is a new product inside their platform, not a rebranding of their marketing site.

